{"uri":"hotshot-dna-extraction-g6vbze6","version_id":"0","protocol_name":"HotSHOT DNA extraction","protocol_name_html":"HotSHOT DNA extraction","is_prepublished":"0","can_edit":"0","parent_id":null,"api_version":"1","is_new_mode":"1","last_modified":"1522216802","type_id":"1","link":"","fork_id":"","public_fork_note":"","number_of_steps":"4","has_versions":"0","first_published_date":"1486847216","publish_date":"2017-02-11 21:06:56","documents":null,"have_protocol_in_step":"0","is_protocol_in_step":"0","vendor_name":"Contributed by users","vendor_link":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io","vendor_logo":"\/img\/vendors\/1.png","mod_mins":"-45","mod_secs":"1","description":"<p>Rapid, cheap, and effective DNA extraction for PCR. Easily scaled up to 96-well plates. This originates with Truett et al (2000) <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\/pubmed\/?term=10907076%5Buid%5D\" target=\"_blank\">PMID:10907076<\/a><\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>This protocol is very well tested by many labs for subsequent PCR amplification. For PCR it does not matter that DNA also has protein, is in low concentration, and is fragmented. This is a very robust DNA preparation method.<\/p>\n<p>It is not difficult to do 960 DNA extractions per day (10 plates), the major determinant is tissue handling.<\/p>\n<div title=\"Page 1\">\n<div>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<table style=\"width: 483px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 248px;\">\u00a0<strong>Alkaline Lysis Solution (pH 12)<\/strong><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 235px;\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For 100 ml add<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 248px;\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>25 mM NaOH<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 235px;\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>25 ml of 100 mM NaOH<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 248px;\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>0.2 mM Na2EDTA<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 235px;\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>0.4 ml of 50 mM Na2EDTA (pH 8)<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 248px;\">\u00a0<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 235px;\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>74.6 ml of ddH2O<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<table style=\"width: 481px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 243px;\"><strong>\u00a0Neutralizing Solution (pH 5)<\/strong><\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 238px;\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For 100 ml add:<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 243px;\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>40 mM Tris-HCl<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 238px;\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>630 mg of Tris-HCl<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 243px;\">\u00a0<\/td>\n<td style=\"width: 238px;\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>100 ml of ddH2O<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>Notes:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Prepare alkaline lysis solution fresh each day<\/li>\n<li>Neutralizing solution is stable at room temperature for long periods (months-years)<\/li>\n<li>Tris-HCL is NOT Tris-base<\/li>\n<li>The main cause of failure is too much tissue for the volume of alkaline lysis solution<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div>","is_bookmarked":"0","can_reassign":"1","before_start":"","has_guidelines":"0","materials":[],"warning":"","version_class":"5045","public":"1","is_owner":"1","is_original_owner":"1","created_on":"1486842857","protocol_affiliation":"EvoHull group, University of Hull, UK","affiliation":"University of Hull, UK","doi":"dx.doi.org\/10.17504\/protocols.io.g6vbze6","doi_status":"2","changed_fork_steps":null,"profile_url":"Dave-x2036443","protocol_img":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/ib3xn5.png","profile_image":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/cu7xn5.jpg","full_name":"Dave Lunt","created_by":"Dave Lunt","private_link":"9E157F220ED7D7C74B1D2FFD628C095D","original_img":"1","username":"dave-lunt","is_retracted":"0","retraction_reason":null,"plos_id":null,"manuscript_citation":null,"journal_name":null,"is_donations_disabled":"0","is_donations_disabled_by_user":"9","item_record_id":208779,"fork_info":[],"compare_forks":[],"protocols":[],"groups":[{"group_id":"152","group_uri":"evohull","group_name":"EvoHull","group_logo":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/ibsxn5.png","requested_uid":null,"request_flag":null,"my_request":"1"}],"number_of_shared_runs":[],"ownership_history":[],"keywords":"","transfer_to_user":[],"sub_transfer":false,"is_transfer_pending":false,"number_of_bookmarks":"0","collections":[],"tags":[],"archived":0,"sub_authors":[],"sub_protocols_number":0,"can_edit_shared":0,"shared_runs":[],"is_shared_run":0,"is_shared":1,"banner":null,"contact_badges":[{"badge_id":"2","badge_image":"\/img\/badges\/bronze.svg","badge_description":"Author!"},{"badge_id":"5","badge_image":"\/img\/badges\/earlyadopter.svg","badge_description":"Early adopter"},{"badge_id":"6","badge_image":"\/img\/badges\/socialbutterfly.svg","badge_description":"Social butterfly"}],"number_of_comments":0,"big_protocol_img":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/ib2xn5.png","big_protocol_img_ofn":"hotshot.png","is_locked":0,"is_locked_by":false,"authors":"Dave Lunt","authors_list":[{"name":"Dave Lunt","affiliation":"EvoHull group, University of Hull, UK","username":null,"profile_image":null}],"user":{"profile_image":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/cu7xn5.jpg","username":"dave-lunt","full_name":"Dave Lunt","created_by":"Dave Lunt"},"access":{"can_view":"1","can_remove":"0","can_add":"0","can_edit":0,"can_publish":0,"can_get_doi":0,"can_share":"0","can_move":"1","can_transfer":"1","can_download":"1","is_locked":"0"},"is_contact_suspended":0,"guidelines":"","status_id":"1","is_research":"1","status_info":null,"steps":[{"id":"321981","is_changed":"0","original_id":"0","is_skipped":"0","is_checked":"0","guid":"FA4205150BBE402684C63CD572E73A6D","previous_guid":null,"previous_id":"0","last_modified":"1486845663","components":[{"component_id":"479645","previous_id":0,"original_id":"0","guid":"F3DB9B7F84E64811AC539924A5CD13BD","previous_guid":null,"component_type_id":"1","data_id":"0","data":"<p>Add 50ul of alkaline lysis solution into 0.2ml PCR tubes, or 96 well PCR plate, and add tissue.<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>Solutions are detailed\u00a0in the Description section<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>The volumes of solution and tissue are the major determinant of how well your DNA extraction will work. Too much tissue is the most common cause of PCR failure following HotSHOT. Sub-visible amounts up to tissue the size of a full stop . try 25ul. Tissue the size of a 10pt Arial font o might need 75ul. Begin by trying a few\u00a0tissue to solution ratios until you are familiar. Too much tissue is the most common cause of failure for\u00a0HotSHOT beginners.<\/p>","order_id":"0","name":"Description","data_by_id":"0","type_id":"1","source_data":{"description":"<p>Add 50ul of alkaline lysis solution into 0.2ml PCR tubes, or 96 well PCR plate, and add tissue.<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>Solutions are detailed\u00a0in the Description section<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>The volumes of solution and tissue are the major determinant of how well your DNA extraction will work. Too much tissue is the most common cause of PCR failure following HotSHOT. Sub-visible amounts up to tissue the size of a full stop . try 25ul. Tissue the size of a 10pt Arial font o might need 75ul. Begin by trying a few\u00a0tissue to solution ratios until you are familiar. Too much tissue is the most common cause of failure for\u00a0HotSHOT beginners.<\/p>"},"is_project":0},{"component_id":"479639","previous_id":"479645","original_id":"0","guid":"14FB763BD3FC461AADCB1061722F863C","previous_guid":"F3DB9B7F84E64811AC539924A5CD13BD","component_type_id":"6","data_id":"0","data":"Place tissue in alkaline lysis solution","order_id":"1","name":"Section","data_by_id":"0","type_id":"6","source_data":{"section":"Place tissue in alkaline lysis solution"},"is_p